narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great class. Worth taking even if you dont need the language requirement.
just like level 2 just a little more speaking and different material obviously, same pace and workload

Spanish 130 is generally a good course. There is class and homework everyday which is kind of a chore and a lot of busy work, but it definitely improves your Spanish. Take it with Diaz. He's great. He's very helpful and makes the class enjoyable.

L3 is a good course that reviews Spanish learned in L2, but with greater depth. There is a lot of emphasis placed on improving reading ability, but the flip side, for better or worse, is that there's less time spent speaking in groups and having discussions.
L3 is a nice review of the material learned in L1 and L2. If you are looking to fulfill the language requirement, or if you want a good review of the Spanish language, I would recommend this course.
Spanish 130 was one of my favorite classes this semester, and I would recommend it to another student, as long as that student wants to study Spanish.
A must take (literally), but really fun. The homework is enjoyable.
I would recommend this course to another student as a great L3 course.
yes, it was interesting and fun and i learned a lot

This course was a good way to improve my Spanish skills. It incorporated basic things such as grammar and vocabulary with cultural practices. This made the class more fun. I would definitely recommend this course to any interested student.
